arcade.potts.agent.cell

Class PottsCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.potts.agent.cell.PottsCell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cell, java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable

    public final class PottsCell
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cell
    Implementation of Cell for potts models.

    PottsCell agents exist in one of five states: quiescent, proliferative, apoptotic, necrotic, or autotic. Each state may be further divided into relevant phases.

    General order of rules for the PottsCell step:

    • update age
    • step state module

    Cell parameters are tracked using a map between the parameter name and value.

    To integrate with the Potts layer, PottsCell agents also contain critical and target volumes and surfaces. Additional parameters specific to each term in the Hamiltonian are tracked by the specific Hamiltonian class instance.

      • updateTarget

        public void updateTarget(double rate,
                         double scale)
        Updates target volume and surface area. When scale is greater than one, volume increases by given rate. When scale is less than one, volume decreases by given rate. If scale is one, sizes are not changed.
        Parameters:
        rate - the rate of change
        scale - the relative final size scaling

      • updateTarget

        public void updateTarget(Enums.Region region,
                         double rate,
                         double scale)
        Updates target volume and surface area for a region.

        If the region is the DEFAULT region, then updates are the same as for a cell without regions.

        Parameters:
        region - the region
        rate - the rate of change
        scale - the relative final size scaling
